  "contentHtml": "<!-- BEGIN COPYRIGHTED TEXT CHUNK --><html><head></head><body><div class=\"chapter\">\n<p>The Mahaniddesa, the first part of the Niddesa of the Khuddaka Nikaya, is a commentary, attributed to Ven. Sariputta, on the <a href=\"/tipitaka/kn/snp#atthakavagga\">Atthakavagga</a> of the Sutta Nipata.</p>\n<p>The translator appears in the square brackets [].</p>\n\n<h1>Selected Suttas</h1>\n<ul class=\"suttaList\">\n\t\n<!-- html_sutta_summary.inc.php -->\n\n<li><a id=\"nm.2.04.olen\"></a><span class=\"sutta_title\"><a href=\"/tipitaka/kn/nm/nm.2.04.olen\" title=\"Translated by Andrew Olendzki\">Nm 2.4: Guhatthaka-suttaniddeso — Upon the Tip of a Needle</a></span>\n\t<span class=\"sutta_ref\">{<a href=\"/tipitaka/sltp/Nidd_I_utf8#pts.042\" title=\"Read the Pali source\" target=\"pali\">Nd i 42</a>}</span>\n\t<span class=\"sutta_trans\">[<a href=\"/tipitaka/kn/nm/nm.2.04.olen\" title=\"Translated by Andrew Olendzki\">Olendzki</a>].</span>\n\t<div class=\"sutta_summary\">In a series of verses of stunning simplicity and elegance, Sariputta describes the fleeting evanescence of the present moment. </div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n\n</body></html>",
